metadata.name: AstroDome
metadata.description:
Growing up in Western Australia I’ve always wanted to visit the Bungle Bungle Range located in the Kimberley.

The ground is scattered with smooth pebbles and limestone beach scenes that come complete with stark white beach sand and the pathways are scattered with elegant Livistona Palms.

The beehive shaped domes are striped with cyanobacteria with the main structure composed of sandstone, deposited millions of years ago!

I was lucky enough to get on the Dream Photography Astro Workshop where we spent 8 days shooting at some epic locations in the East Kimberley, the furtherest region in the North/East of my home-state, Western Australia.

The magical, World Heritage-listed Bungle Bungle Range covers over 400kms of land situated in the Purnululu National Park where the Gija and Jaru people are the Traditional Custodians. 

This is my first astro to be minted, I have a mixture of nerves and pure excitement as I have worked towards increasing my Astro skills since my first shot in 2019!

There will be more…

20% of the sale of this image will be put back in to an arts program in Kununurra.
